{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":857,"text":"You've heard of your I.Q.,\nyour general intelligence,"},{"time":3716,"text":"but what's your Psy-Q?"},{"time":5392,"text":"How much do you know\nabout what makes you tick,"},{"time":7629,"text":"and how good are you\nat predicting other people's behavior"},{"time":10374,"text":"or even your own?"},{"time":11880,"text":"And how much of what you think you know\nabout psychology is wrong?"},{"time":15159,"text":"Let's find out by counting down\nthe top 10 myths of psychology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18947,"text":"You've probably heard it said\nthat when it comes to their psychology,"},{"time":22343,"text":"it's almost as if men are from Mars\nand women are from Venus."},{"time":25235,"text":"But how different\nare men and women really?"},{"time":27264,"text":"To find out, let's start\nby looking at something"},{"time":29518,"text":"on which men and women really do differ"},{"time":31495,"text":"and plotting some psychological\ngender differences on the same scale."},{"time":34943,"text":"One thing men and women\ndo really differ on"},{"time":37116,"text":"is how far they can throw a ball."},{"time":38913,"text":"So if we look at the data for men here,"},{"time":40803,"text":"we see what is called\na normal distribution curve."},{"time":43274,"text":"A few men can throw a ball really far,\nand a few men not far at all,"},{"time":46482,"text":"but most a kind of average distance."},{"time":48252,"text":"And women share\nthe same distribution as well,"},{"time":50416,"text":"but actually there's\nquite a big difference."},{"time":52465,"text":"In fact, the average man\ncan throw a ball further"},{"time":54913,"text":"than about 98 percent of all women."},{"time":56620,"text":"So now let's look at what\nsome psychological gender differences"},{"time":59647,"text":"look like on the same standardized scale."},{"time":62504,"text":"Any psychologist will tell you"},{"time":64090,"text":"that men are better\nat spatial awareness than women --"},{"time":66635,"text":"so things like map-reading, \nfor example -- and it's true,"},{"time":69373,"text":"but let's have a look\nat the size of this difference."},{"time":71863,"text":"It's tiny; the lines are so close\ntogether they almost overlap."},{"time":75250,"text":"In fact, the average woman is better\nthan 33 percent of all men,"},{"time":79244,"text":"and of course, if that was 50 percent,"},{"time":81125,"text":"then the two genders\nwould be exactly equal."},{"time":83181,"text":"It's worth bearing in mind that this\ndifference and the next one I'll show you"},{"time":86839,"text":"are pretty much the biggest\npsychological gender differences"},{"time":89664,"text":"ever discovered in psychology."},{"time":91101,"text":"So here's the next one."},{"time":92212,"text":"Any psychologist will tell you\nthat women are better"},{"time":94650,"text":"with language and grammar than men."},{"time":96315,"text":"So here's performance\non the standardized grammar test."},{"time":98904,"text":"There go the women. There go the men."},{"time":100861,"text":"Again, yes, women are better on average,\nbut the lines are so close"},{"time":104560,"text":"that 33 percent of men\nare better than the average woman,"},{"time":108047,"text":"and again, if it was 50 percent,"},{"time":109720,"text":"that would represent\ncomplete gender equality."},{"time":112462,"text":"So it's not really\na case of Mars and Venus."},{"time":114583,"text":"It's more a case of, if anything,\nMars and Snickers:"},{"time":117250,"text":"basically the same, but one's maybe \nslightly nuttier than the other."},{"time":121612,"text":"I won't say which."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123638,"text":"Now we've got you warmed up."},{"time":125503,"text":"Let's psychoanalyze you using\nthe famous Rorschach inkblot test."},{"time":128539,"text":"So you can probably see two, I dunno,\ntwo bears or two people or something."},{"time":132122,"text":"But what do you think they're doing?"},{"time":133875,"text":"Put your hand up if you think\nthey're saying hello."},{"time":137059,"text":"Not many people. Okay."},{"time":138870,"text":"Put your hands up if you think\nthey are high-fiving."},{"time":141337,"text":"Okay. What if you think they're fighting?"},{"time":143307,"text":"Only a few people there."},{"time":144562,"text":"Okay, so if you think they're\nsaying hello or high-fiving,"},{"time":147639,"text":"then that means you're a friendly person."},{"time":149630,"text":"If you think they're fighting,"},{"time":151220,"text":"you're a bit more of a \nnasty, aggressive person."},{"time":153536,"text":"Are you a lover or a fighter, basically."},{"time":155476,"text":"What about this one?"},{"time":156763,"text":"This isn't really a voting one, so on \nthree everyone shout out what you see."},{"time":160385,"text":"One, two, three.\n(Audience shouting)"},{"time":163549,"text":"I heard hamster. Who said hamster?"},{"time":165241,"text":"That was very worrying."},{"time":166778,"text":"A guy there said hamster."},{"time":168291,"text":"Well, you should see\nsome kind of two-legged animal here,"},{"time":171599,"text":"and then the mirror image of them there."},{"time":173983,"text":"If you didn't, then this means\nthat you have difficulty"},{"time":177414,"text":"processing complex situations\nwhere there's a lot going on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181504,"text":"Except, of course,\nit doesn't mean that at all."},{"time":183729,"text":"Rorschach inkblot tests\nhave basically no validity"},{"time":186400,"text":"when it comes to diagnosing\npeople's personality"},{"time":188675,"text":"and are not used\nby modern-day psychologists."},{"time":191136,"text":"In fact, one recent study found\nthat when you do try"},{"time":194555,"text":"to diagnose people's personalities\nusing Rorschach inkblot tests,"},{"time":197614,"text":"schizophrenia was diagnosed"},{"time":199356,"text":"in about one sixth of apparently\nperfectly normal participants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203349,"text":"So if you didn't do that well on this,"},{"time":206182,"text":"maybe you are not\na very visual type of person."},{"time":208736,"text":"So let's do another\nquick quiz to find out."},{"time":211105,"text":"When making a cake, do you prefer to --\nso hands up for each one again --"},{"time":214883,"text":"do you prefer to use\na recipe book with pictures?"},{"time":217652,"text":"Yeah, a few people."},{"time":219672,"text":"Have a friend talk you through?"},{"time":222412,"text":"Or have a go, making it up\nas you go along?"},{"time":225075,"text":"Quite a few people there."},{"time":226567,"text":"Okay, so if you said A,"},{"time":228287,"text":"then this means that you\nare a visual learner"},{"time":230459,"text":"and you learn best when information\nis presented in a visual style."},{"time":233987,"text":"If you said B, it means\nyou're an auditory learner,"},{"time":236569,"text":"that you learn best when information\nis presented to you in an auditory format."},{"time":240294,"text":"And if you said C, it means\nthat you're a kinesthetic learner,"},{"time":243229,"text":"that you learn best when you get stuck in\nand do things with your hands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246630,"text":"Except, of course,\nas you've probably guessed,"},{"time":248788,"text":"that it doesn't, because\nthe whole thing is a complete myth."},{"time":251607,"text":"Learning styles are made up and are \nnot supported by scientific evidence."},{"time":255465,"text":"So we know this because in\ntightly controlled experimental studies,"},{"time":259021,"text":"when learners are given material to learn"},{"time":261142,"text":"either in their preferred style\nor an opposite style,"},{"time":263762,"text":"it makes no difference at all to the\namount of information that they retain."},{"time":267338,"text":"And if you think about it\nfor just a second,"},{"time":269404,"text":"it's just obvious\nthat this has to be true."},{"time":271482,"text":"It's obvious that\nthe best presentation format"},{"time":274054,"text":"depends not on you,\nbut on what you're trying to learn."},{"time":277357,"text":"Could you learn to drive a car,\nfor example,"},{"time":279479,"text":"just by listening to someone\ntelling you what to do"},{"time":281897,"text":"with no kinesthetic experience?"},{"time":283525,"text":"Could you solve simultaneous equations"},{"time":285341,"text":"by talking them through in your head\nand without writing them down?"},{"time":288487,"text":"Could you revise \nfor your architecture exams"},{"time":290588,"text":"using interpretive dance\nif you're a kinesthetic learner?"},{"time":293261,"text":"No. What you need to do \nis match the material to be learned"},{"time":296202,"text":"to the presentation format, not you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299977,"text":"I know many of you are A-level students"},{"time":302126,"text":"that will have recently gotten\nyour GCSE results."},{"time":304418,"text":"And if you didn't quite get\nwhat you were hoping for,"},{"time":306976,"text":"then you can't really blame\nyour learning style,"},{"time":309323,"text":"but one thing that you might want\nto think about blaming is your genes."},{"time":312950,"text":"So what this is all about is a\nrecent study at University College London"},{"time":316635,"text":"found that 58 percent of the variation"},{"time":319189,"text":"between different students\nand their GCSE results"},{"time":322440,"text":"was down to genetic factors."},{"time":324097,"text":"That sounds like a very precise figure,\nso how can we tell?"},{"time":327233,"text":"Well, when we want to unpack\nthe relative contributions"},{"time":330738,"text":"of genes and the environment,"},{"time":332842,"text":"what we can do is do a twin study."},{"time":335071,"text":"So identical twins share\n100 percent of their environment"},{"time":338647,"text":"and 100 percent of their genes,"},{"time":340551,"text":"whereas non-identical twins\nshare 100 percent of their environment,"},{"time":343773,"text":"but just like any brother and sister,\nshare only 50 percent of their genes."},{"time":347509,"text":"So by comparing how similar\nGCSE results are in identical twins"},{"time":351707,"text":"versus non-identical twins,"},{"time":354018,"text":"and doing some clever math,"},{"time":355364,"text":"we can an idea of how much variation\nand performance is due to the environment"},{"time":359265,"text":"and how much is due to genes."},{"time":361401,"text":"And it turns out that it's\nabout 58 percent due to genes."},{"time":365178,"text":"So this isn't to undermine the hard work\nthat you and your teachers here put in."},{"time":368941,"text":"If you didn't quite get the GCSE results\nthat you were hoping for,"},{"time":372072,"text":"then you can always try blaming\nyour parents, or at least their genes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376578,"text":"One thing that you shouldn't blame"},{"time":378606,"text":"is being a left-brained\nor right-brained learner,"},{"time":381068,"text":"because again, this is a myth."},{"time":382879,"text":"So the myth here is that\nthe left brain is logical,"},{"time":385636,"text":"it's good with equations like this,"},{"time":387435,"text":"and the right brain is more creative,\nso the right brain is better at music."},{"time":391534,"text":"But again, this is a myth\nbecause nearly everything that you do"},{"time":394465,"text":"involves nearly all parts\nof your brain talking together,"},{"time":397275,"text":"even just the most mundane thing\nlike having a normal conversation."},{"time":400595,"text":"However, perhaps one reason\nwhy this myth has survived"},{"time":403938,"text":"is that there is\na slight grain of truth to it."},{"time":406180,"text":"So a related version of the myth"},{"time":407790,"text":"is that left-handed people are\nmore creative than right-handed people,"},{"time":411073,"text":"which kind of makes sense because\nyour brain controls the opposite hands,"},{"time":414527,"text":"so left-handed people,"},{"time":415887,"text":"the right side of the brain\nis slightly more active"},{"time":418313,"text":"than the left-hand side of the brain,"},{"time":420118,"text":"and the idea is the right-hand side\nis more creative."},{"time":422606,"text":"Now, it isn't true per se"},{"time":424003,"text":"that left-handed people are more creative\nthan right-handed people."},{"time":427204,"text":"What is true that ambidextrous people,"},{"time":429619,"text":"or people who use both hands\nfor different tasks,"},{"time":432312,"text":"are more creative thinkers\nthan one-handed people,"},{"time":436074,"text":"because being ambidextrous involves"},{"time":437807,"text":"having both sides of the brain\ntalk to each other a lot,"},{"time":440536,"text":"which seems to be involved\nin creating flexible thinking."},{"time":444298,"text":"The myth of the creative left-hander"},{"time":446113,"text":"arises from the fact\nthat being ambidextrous"},{"time":448171,"text":"is more common amongst \nleft-handers than right-handers,"},{"time":451298,"text":"so a grain of truth in the idea\nof the creative left-hander,"},{"time":454347,"text":"but not much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455694,"text":"A related myth that you've\nprobably heard of"},{"time":458131,"text":"is that we only use\n10 percent of our brains."},{"time":460504,"text":"This is, again, a complete myth."},{"time":462030,"text":"Nearly everything that we do,\neven the most mundane thing,"},{"time":464749,"text":"uses nearly all of our brains."}]},{"cues":[{"time":466932,"text":"That said, it is of course true"},{"time":470693,"text":"that most of us don't use our brainpower\nquite as well as we could."},{"time":475273,"text":"So what could we do\nto boost our brainpower?"},{"time":478239,"text":"Maybe we could listen\nto a nice bit of Mozart."},{"time":480377,"text":"Have you heard of the idea\nof the Mozart effect?"},{"time":483095,"text":"So the idea is that listening \nto Mozart makes you smarter"},{"time":486052,"text":"and improves your \nperformance on I.Q. tests."},{"time":488221,"text":"Now again, what's interesting\nabout this myth"},{"time":490326,"text":"is that although it's basically a myth,\nthere is a grain of truth to it."},{"time":493767,"text":"So the original study found that"},{"time":495541,"text":"participants who were played\nMozart music for a few minutes"},{"time":499322,"text":"did better on a subsequent I.Q. test"},{"time":501621,"text":"than participants who simply\nsat in silence."},{"time":505034,"text":"But a follow-up study recruited\nsome people who liked Mozart music"},{"time":508758,"text":"and then another group of people"},{"time":510539,"text":"who were fans of \nthe horror stories of Stephen King."},{"time":513207,"text":"And they played the people\nthe music or the stories."},{"time":516771,"text":"The people who preferred\nMozart music to the stories"},{"time":519279,"text":"got a bigger I.Q. boost\nfrom the Mozart than the stories,"},{"time":522010,"text":"but the people who preferred\nthe stories to the Mozart music"},{"time":524848,"text":"got a bigger I.Q. boost\nfrom listening to the Stephen King stories"},{"time":527955,"text":"than the Mozart music."},{"time":529170,"text":"So the truth is that listening\nto something that you enjoy"},{"time":531933,"text":"perks you up a bit\nand gives you a temporary I.Q. boost"},{"time":535184,"text":"on a narrow range of tasks."},{"time":537111,"text":"There's no suggestion that\nlistening to Mozart,"},{"time":539479,"text":"or indeed Stephen King stories,"},{"time":541104,"text":"is going to make you any smarter\nin the long run."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544526,"text":"Another version of the Mozart myth"},{"time":547466,"text":"is that listening to Mozart can make you\nnot only cleverer but healthier, too."},{"time":552324,"text":"Unfortunately, this doesn't\nseem to be true"},{"time":554392,"text":"of someone who listened\nto the music of Mozart almost every day,"},{"time":557451,"text":"Mozart himself,"},{"time":559169,"text":"who suffered from gonorrhea,\nsmallpox, arthritis,"},{"time":562149,"text":"and, what most people think eventually\nkilled him in the end, syphilis."},{"time":566673,"text":"This suggests that Mozart\nshould have bit more careful, perhaps,"},{"time":570035,"text":"when choosing his sexual partners."},{"time":572613,"text":"But how do we choose a partner?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":574772,"text":"So a myth that I have to say\nis sometimes spread a bit by sociologists"},{"time":579798,"text":"is that our preferences in a romantic \npartner are a product of our culture,"},{"time":583421,"text":"that they're very culturally specific."},{"time":585352,"text":"But in fact, the data don't back this up."},{"time":587496,"text":"A famous study surveyed people from\n[37] different cultures across the globe,"},{"time":591541,"text":"from Americans to Zulus,"},{"time":593117,"text":"on what they look for in a partner."},{"time":595483,"text":"And in every single culture\nacross the globe,"},{"time":597852,"text":"men placed more value\non physical attractiveness in a partner"},{"time":601567,"text":"than did women,"},{"time":602867,"text":"and in every single culture, too,"},{"time":604608,"text":"women placed more importance than did men\non ambition and high earning power."},{"time":609222,"text":"In every culture, too,"},{"time":610605,"text":"men preferred women\nwho were younger than themselves,"},{"time":613130,"text":"an average of, I think it was 2.66 years,"},{"time":615939,"text":"and in every culture, too,"},{"time":617588,"text":"women preferred men\nwho were older than them,"},{"time":620188,"text":"so an average of 3.42 years,"},{"time":622998,"text":"which is why we've got here\n\"Everybody needs a Sugar Daddy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":626713,"text":"So moving on from trying\nto score with a partner"},{"time":629290,"text":"to trying to score in basketball\nor football or whatever your sport is."},{"time":633212,"text":"The myth here is that sportsmen go through\nhot-hand streaks, Americans call them,"},{"time":637353,"text":"or purple patches,\nwe sometimes say in England,"},{"time":639553,"text":"where they just can't miss,\nlike this guy here."},{"time":642393,"text":"But in fact, what happens is that\nif you analyze the pattern"},{"time":646077,"text":"of hits and misses statistically,"},{"time":647865,"text":"it turns out that it's\nnearly always at random."},{"time":650164,"text":"Your brain creates patterns\nfrom the randomness."},{"time":652579,"text":"If you toss a coin,"},{"time":653936,"text":"a streak of heads or tails is going \nto come out somewhere in the randomness,"},{"time":657572,"text":"and because the brain likes to see\npatterns where there are none,"},{"time":660683,"text":"we look at these streaks\nand attribute meanings to them"},{"time":663284,"text":"and say, \"Yeah he's really on form today,\""},{"time":665591,"text":"whereas actually you would\nget the same pattern"},{"time":667901,"text":"if you were just getting\nhits and misses at random."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671406,"text":"So an exception to this, however,\nis penalty shootouts."},{"time":674872,"text":"A recent study looking\nat penalty shootouts in football"},{"time":677957,"text":"shows that players who represent countries"},{"time":679977,"text":"with a very bad record\nin penalty shootouts,"},{"time":682601,"text":"like, for example, England,"},{"time":684784,"text":"tend to be quicker to take their shots\nthan countries with a better record,"},{"time":688545,"text":"and presumably as a result,\nthey're more likely to miss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691865,"text":"Which raises the question"},{"time":693560,"text":"of if there's any way that we\ncould improve people's performance."},{"time":696949,"text":"And one thing you might think about doing"},{"time":698947,"text":"is punishing people for their misses\nand seeing if that improves them."},{"time":702366,"text":"This idea, the effect that punishment\ncan improve performance,"},{"time":705998,"text":"is what participants\nthought they were testing"},{"time":708204,"text":"in Milgram's famous learning\nand punishment experiment"},{"time":710736,"text":"that you've probably heard about\nif you're a psychology student."},{"time":713744,"text":"The story goes that participants\nwere prepared to give"},{"time":716566,"text":"what they believed to be fatal\nelectric shocks to a fellow participant"},{"time":719867,"text":"when they got a question wrong,"},{"time":721888,"text":"just because someone\nin a white coat told them to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724697,"text":"But this story is a myth\nfor three reasons."},{"time":727112,"text":"Firstly and most crucially, the lab coat\nwasn't white, it was in fact grey."},{"time":732016,"text":"Secondly, the participants\nwere told before the study"},{"time":736423,"text":"and reminded any time\nthey raised a concern,"},{"time":738930,"text":"that although the shocks were painful,\nthey were not fatal"},{"time":741763,"text":"and indeed caused\nno permanent damage whatsoever."},{"time":744505,"text":"And thirdly, participants\ndidn't give the shocks"},{"time":746825,"text":"just because someone\nin the coat told them to."},{"time":749473,"text":"When they were interviewed\nafter the study,"},{"time":751515,"text":"all the participants said\nthat they firmly believed"},{"time":754023,"text":"that the learning and punishment study\nserved a worthy scientific purpose"},{"time":757807,"text":"which would have\nenduring gains for science"},{"time":760245,"text":"as opposed to the momentary nonfatal\ndiscomfort caused to the participants."}]},{"cues":[{"time":767025,"text":"Okay, so I've been talking\nfor about 12 minutes now,"},{"time":769603,"text":"and you've probably been \nsitting there listening to me,"},{"time":772289,"text":"analyzing my speech patterns \nand body language"},{"time":774509,"text":"and trying to work out if you should\ntake any notice of what I'm saying,"},{"time":778116,"text":"whether I'm telling the truth\nor whether I'm lying,"},{"time":780577,"text":"but if so you've\nprobably completely failed,"},{"time":782759,"text":"because although we all think\nwe can catch a liar"},{"time":785104,"text":"from their body language\nand speech patterns,"},{"time":787197,"text":"hundreds of psychological tests\nover the years have shown"},{"time":789870,"text":"that all of us, including\npolice officers and detectives,"},{"time":792561,"text":"are basically at chance when it comes\nto detecting lies from body language"},{"time":796061,"text":"and verbal patterns."},{"time":797642,"text":"Interestingly, there is one exception:"},{"time":799686,"text":"TV appeals for missing relatives."},{"time":801938,"text":"It's quite easy to predict\nwhen the relatives are missing"},{"time":804923,"text":"and when the appealers have in fact\nmurdered the relatives themselves."},{"time":808254,"text":"So hoax appealers are more likely\nto shake their heads, to look away,"},{"time":811769,"text":"and to make errors in their speech,"},{"time":813483,"text":"whereas genuine appealers are more likely"},{"time":815498,"text":"to express hope that the person\nwill return safely"},{"time":817843,"text":"and to avoid brutal language."},{"time":819584,"text":"So, for example, they might say\n\"taken from us\" rather than \"killed.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":824187,"text":"Speaking of which,\nit's about time I killed this talk,"},{"time":826844,"text":"but before I do, I just want \nto give you in 30 seconds"},{"time":830052,"text":"the overarching myth of psychology."},{"time":833423,"text":"So the myth is that psychology is just\na collection of interesting theories,"},{"time":837720,"text":"all of which say something useful\nand all of which have something to offer."},{"time":841241,"text":"What I hope to have shown you\nin the past few minutes"},{"time":843740,"text":"is that this isn't true."},{"time":845325,"text":"What we need to do is assess\npsychological theories"},{"time":848584,"text":"by seeing what predictions they make,"},{"time":850468,"text":"whether that is that listening to Mozart\nmakes you smarter,"},{"time":853289,"text":"that you learn better when information is\npresented in your preferred learning style"},{"time":858056,"text":"or whatever it is, all of these\nare testable empirical predictions,"},{"time":861521,"text":"and the only way we can make progress"},{"time":863306,"text":"is to test these predictions\nagainst the data"},{"time":865426,"text":"in tightly controlled\nexperimental studies."},{"time":867755,"text":"And it's only by doing so\nthat we can hope to discover"},{"time":870889,"text":"which of these theories\nare well supported,"},{"time":873513,"text":"and which, like all the ones\nI've told you about today, are myths."}]},{"cues":[{"time":876903,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":878412,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}